0a\u000aWhat if there was a community, but the game wasn't widely known (yet)? Then you would need the people I talked about at the beginning to attract new people.\u000a","count":5,"avatar":"/thumbcache/100/100/www.wetgenes.com/icon/28568","group":0,"author":"28568@id.wetgenes.com","replies":[{"pagecount":0,"text":"ie. content does not matter, only the shit surrounding it.\u000a","count":0,"avatar":"/thumbcache/100/100/www.wetgenes.com/icon/14","group":91602,"author":"14@id.wetgenes.com","created":1296688498.722,"spam":0,"url":"/blog/85601","cache":{"user":{"authentication":{},"name":"shi","admin":"false","id":"14@id.wetgenes.com","email":"14@id.wetgenes.com","info":{},"updated":1292487239.611,"flavour":"wetgenes","created":1292487239.607,"kind":"user.data"}},"type":"ok","title":"Feedback is fractal in nature.","id":99601,"kind":"note.comments","good":0,"media":0,"updated":1296688498.722},{"pagecount":0,"text":"I'm saying that sometimes it takes a few people to show the others what can be made out of something.\u000a\u000aIf I give Photoshop to someone, and they don't really know how to use it, they will say that it's a nice image editor but that Paint loads way faster. They will miss all the things you can do with it. Then you show them an image and say it was made with Photoshop, and they are all \u0022Wow, that's nice!\u0022, and then you show them tutorials and they start doing incredible stuff. (I hope my analogy isn't too bad.)\u000a\u000aThere are here two different types of content: the tools to create, and the creations themselves. The first are done by the programmers, the second by people using the program.\u000a","count":0,"avatar":"/thumbcache/100/100/www.wetgenes.com/icon/28568","group":91602,"author":"28568@id.wetgenes.com","created":1296850156.186,"spam":0,"url":"/blog/85601","cache":{"user":{"authentication":{},"name":"Kohaku","admin":false,"id":"28568@id.wetgenes.com","email":"28568@id.wetgenes.com","info":{},"updated":1294403173.499,"flavour":"we